manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Usage Guidelines Rear-Facing Mode: 25-43 in, 14-50 lbs, child able to sit upright alone Forward-Facing Mode: 30-49 in, 22-65 lbs, 2+ years recommended (1 year minimum) Can be used from birth with infant-thingy insert (sold separately) Included in box: Fllo, Anti-Rebound Bar, Manual Accessories available for purchase separately. Drink-thingy, Infant-thingy infant insert, Weelee travel bag, Cleaning Kit, Mat-thingy. Clek Fllo Convertible Car Seat, with LATCH, Anti-Rebound Bar, EACT Crumble Zone Technology and 9-Year Expiration The Compact Convertible Car Seat At less than 17 inches, Fllo makes it easy to ride 3-across. One of the safest narrow car seats available, it’s packed with industry-leading safety features, including a steel anti-rebound bar, Clek’s patented energy management system – and advanced side-impact protection with deep side wings, energy-absorbing foam layers and an adjustable structural headrest. Free of Halogenated Flame Retardants, Because We're Parents Too. Like all Clek Car Seats, all Fllo models are free of brominated and chlorinated flame retardants, while Mammoth and Railroad models are free of any added flame retardants. Fllo is proudly designed, engineered, and made in Canada.

Get The Most Out Of Your Back Seat At less than 17 in wide, Fllo provides space that makes 3-across seating possible in most vehicles. Extended Rear-Facing Designed to international best practices for extended rear-facing, which is to accommodate children in a rear-facing seating position until their 4th birthday. Automotive Inspired EACT Safety Technology The EACT (Energy-Absorbing Crumple Technology) safety technology reduces the forces transmitted to a child in a collision using aluminum honeycomb deformable cores integrated into the seat base.

Integrated Flip Foot Integrated Flip foot for rear-facing installation. Advanced Side-Impact Protection Protects the child in a side-impact collision with its adjustable headrest, deep side wings, inner and outer energy absorbing foam layers, and metal substructure. Steel Anti-Rebound Bar Included for enhanced safety performance, in rear-facing mode, Fllo’s Anti-Rebound bar improves stability by limiting rotation of the child seat, helping protect your child’s head from impact in the case of a collision. It also provides for a snug installation, nesting into the flat portion of the vehicle seat, and offers more legroom for the child. Fabric Options for Every Family Fllo features fabric options that suit your child's personality and match their style (or your car!). Our C-Zero Plus Performance fabrics are GREENGUARD Gold Certified and provide resistance to water-based stains using an innovative fluorine-free formula that’s free of halogenated flame retardants. Mammoth (featuring a blend of Merino wool + TENCEL) and Railroad are flame-retardant free, OEKO-TEX Standard 100 certified, and free of PFAS, PFOA, PFC and PFOS chemicals.

Clek car seats are proudly manufactured in Ontario, Canada. Clek is a Canadian based manufacturer of child passenger safety seats that combine safety with ease-of-use and modern style. Born out of a global automotive supplier, Clek offers the superior design, engineering best practices, world-class manufacturing, and craftsmanship found in luxury automotive seating today. We Make Car Seats for Parents Like Us Ride safe. Ride ride. Ride on. Safety: it’s the reason we’re doing this in the first place – to protect the wellbeing of our children and yours. From thoughtful design to impact-reducing materials, all of our baby and toddler car seats and booster car seats are equipped with innovative safety features. Our car seats aren’t just functional. They’re designed to make a statement, because you shouldn’t have to sacrifice style for safety. Made in Canada 9-year expiration Free of Halogonated Flame Retardants Certified for use on an aircraft (FAA certified) Recyclable through Clek's Car Seat Recycling Program Package Dimensions: 31 x 20 17.25 in, 38 lbs Product Dimensions + Weight: 24 x 16.9 x 16 in, 25 lbs

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2021
reviews.reviewText: This is a great car seat with lots of room. Baby doesn’t complain when going for a ride and feels like a “big kid” in it. We specifically ordered this seat for its ability to fit 3 across. We have this seat, a Diono FF and an empty seat in a Jeep Wrangler JKU. The seat was the shorter front to back than a Diono and yet still seems plenty roomy. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Top rated seat but pain to install
reviews.reviewText: Purchased because is top rated seat and can go 3-across in a Corolla. Lot more leg room than other seats, but a real pain to put together and install.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars March 2022 manufacturers date
reviews.reviewText: The seat I ordered from Albee baby is great. The only thing is the manufacture date is 3/22/2022. Already lost one year of use as its only good for 9 years after manufacturing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 31, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Wow, to clean I have to perform car seat surgery!!!!
reviews.reviewText: I bought two of these for my twins. It was really expensive, but looked nice! First up performance fabric is a joke and this car seat got dirty so much quicker and doesn’t wipe clean nicely.So, to clean it, wow, just wow! You have to completely dismantle the product, like seriously! This is made for babies and up. You are going to want to clean it and regularly. Not this car seat. Avoid like the plague!!! I was my car seats often (not this one, because it is so hard, we are talking screw driver and dismantling a million tabs and pulling plastic apart!) no way! No way! Would I ever buy this car seat again. It is stiff, hard to adjust and this cleaning is a joke! I have had britax car seats, and uppa baby maxi cosi, and chicco. This is my least favorite! I am going throw away almost 1,000.00 worth of car seat because I can’t stand this! It is not for the parent that like to clean car seats regularly. And this fabric is a joke. I can’t believe how dirty these are and it hasn’t even been a year and I have been wiping them regularly but got them out and they are disgusting!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 4, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love this seat
reviews.reviewText: My second Clek Fllo. Love it! I drive a CRV. Rear facing behind driver pretty impossible. Rear facing behind passenger doable. Easy to install, super easy to keep clean! I travel with it using the clek wheelie bag and it’s so easy…. Otherwise it’s a heavy seat you don’t want to be moving between cars every day

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not worth it.
reviews.reviewText: This car seat is very high and did not fit in our car. Also seems very uncomfortable. Had to return since we weren’t able to use it. Also, did not get a full refund for what we paid for it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Seems solid, but damaged my leather seats
reviews.reviewText: Just got this car seat, so can’t really say how it will work out over time. It feels well-made, and very solid, and we like the material (we got the Thunder one). Unfortunately, I didn’t buy the “mat thingy” Clek also makes right away,. In my car (2016 Tesla Model S), the only viable position for this seat is the center, and that means there are only seatbelts, no LATCH hooks. In order to get a secure fit, I keep on tightening the seat belt until it moved by less than 1” - as the directions indicated. Three days later, I took the seat back out of the car, and my leather seats had some pretty severe indentations from the underside of the seat.I really don’t understand why the base of the car seat would do that to a car. This is why I’m subtracting a star. Either don’t damage my car, or include the mat thingy in the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Only buy if you hate your child
reviews.reviewText: I picked this seat because it was safe well no it is not. My child screams when put in the seat. And driving down the road they fell asleep and I look back to see my babies head folded forward. And Clek tells me this is safe… no I about had a heart attack! I had to pull over as fast as I could. I can’t let my baby sleep in this seat unless I can hold their head. It is fully reclined and meets every requirement the Clek told me to do. And my child has full head control, they are even able to sit on their own. Please for the love of your baby don’t buy this. I am now stuck with 2 of them and Clek won’t take them back one massive bill and a pissed off spouse that I spent so much on awful seats. O and now I need to by new seats that my baby can actually ride in. I hope to save even one baby and parent from the headache that is this seat!!!! If you still want this seat you must not love your child.
